    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka Treasuries yields up, 3-months rise to 32.11-pct",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s Treasuries yields rose across maturities at Tuesday\u2019s auction with the 12-month yield up 403 basis points to 32.11 percent data from the state debt office showed.",
        "The cut off for the three months are estimated at 35 percent.",
        "A day earlier the market was confused with the cut off for the 7 year bond going up steeply.",
        "The 6-month yield went up 227 basis points to 31.01 percent with 1,802 million rupees raised.",
        "The 12-month yield went up only 1.76 percent with 2,059 million raised.",
        "The 6 and 12 month bills are available on tap for the public.  (Colombo/July12/2022)"
      ],
